  "snapshot": "os",
  "instruction": "You are bootstrapping a new micro-service using the central deployment configuration at ~/Desktop/deploy_config.json. Every action you take must be driven by values from that file — do not use any hard-coded values that differ from what is in the config. Complete all four steps: (1) OS — create the log directory specified in the config's 'logDir' field (/tmp/fastapi_logs/), then write ~/Desktop/env_summary.txt with exactly these two lines taken from the config: 'project=FastAPI Service' and 'author=dev_team'. (2) VS Code — apply the settings from the config to VS Code User Settings: set editor.tabSize to the 'tabSize' field (2), set editor.rulers to a single-element array with the 'maxLineLength' value (88), and add each directory in the 'excludeDirs' list (__pycache__, .env, venv) to files.exclude mapped to true. (3) Chrome — open the URL stored in the config's 'docsUrl' field (https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/) in a new Chrome tab.",
  "source": "authors",
  "config": [
    {
